---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Regulated Benchmarking Services - Alert Energy" description="Expert building energy benchmarking compliance for DC, Chicago, Denver, Vancouver, and Toronto. Accurate filings backed by M&V rigor.">

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="bg-navy-800 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Our Core Service</p>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight mb-6">
          Benchmarking compliance,<br/>handled for you.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-navy-200 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          More and more cities require buildings to report energy use every year. The rules vary by city,
          the paperwork is tedious, and missing a deadline can mean real penalties.
          We take care of all of it so you can focus on running your building.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS BENCHMARKING -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-4">What Is Regulated Benchmarking?</h2>
          <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            In plain terms, it means your city requires you to track and report your building's energy
            and water use. Most places use <a href="https://www.energystar.gov/buildings/benchmark" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-700 underline">ENERGY STAR Portfolio Manager</a> for reporting, but the tricky
            part is everything else: pulling together 12 months of utility data, making sure it is right,
            navigating the right portals, and hitting your deadline.
          </p>
          <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed">
            Get it wrong and you face penalties. Get it right and you have a solid baseline that helps
            you make smarter energy decisions going forward. That is where we come in.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy-800 mb-4">Sound familiar? We can help.</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.834-1.964-.834-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-navy-600 text-sm">Incomplete or inaccurate utility data from multiple providers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.834-1.964-.834-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-navy-600 text-sm">Confusing jurisdiction-specific rules, portals, and formats</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.834-1.964-.834-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-navy-600 text-sm">Missing deadlines and facing escalating penalties</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.834-1.964-.834-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-navy-600 text-sm">Previous filings that may not withstand a compliance audit</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.834-1.964-.834-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-navy-600 text-sm">No clear path from compliance data to real energy savings</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CITY-SPECIFIC EXPERTISE -->
  <section id="cities" class="bg-slate-50 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-14">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-3">We Know the Rules in Your City</h2>
        <p class="text-navy-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Every city is different, and cookie-cutter approaches don't cut it.
          We know the local regs, portals, and common pitfalls in each market we serve.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- DC -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
            <div class="shrink-0">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-navy-800 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="text-amber-400 font-heading font-bold text-lg">DC</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-2">Washington, D.C.</h3>
              <p class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Deadline: May 1, 2026 | <a href="https://doee.dc.gov/service/building-energy-performance-standards-beps" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:underline">BEPS Compliance</a></p>
              <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed">
                DC has moved beyond simple reporting into Building Energy Performance Standards (BEPS).
                This means benchmarking is no longer just a disclosure exercise -- it sets the foundation
                for mandatory performance targets. We ensure your DC benchmarking not only meets the
                immediate filing requirement but positions you correctly for BEPS compliance and avoids
                costly surprises down the road.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chicago -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
            <div class="shrink-0">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-navy-800 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="text-amber-400 font-heading font-bold text-lg">CHI</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-2">Chicago, IL</h3>
              <p class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Deadline: June 1, 2026 | <a href="https://www.chicago.gov/city/en/progs/env/building-energy-benchmarking---transparency.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:underline">Energy Benchmarking Ordinance (Ch. 18-4)</a></p>
              <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed">
                Chicago is unique in requiring an accredited professional to verify benchmarking data.
                It is not enough to simply submit -- the data must be certified. We handle the full
                process from data collection through professional verification, ensuring your filing
                meets the Ordinance requirements and withstands city review.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Denver -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
            <div class="shrink-0">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-navy-800 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="text-amber-400 font-heading font-bold text-lg">DEN</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-2">Denver, CO</h3>
              <p class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Deadline: June 1, 2026 | <a href="https://www.denvergov.org/Government/Agencies-Departments-Offices/Agencies-Departments-Offices-Directory/Climate-Action-Sustainability-Resiliency/Energize-Denver" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:underline">Energize Denver</a></p>
              <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed">
                The Energize Denver ordinance combines benchmarking with performance targets that
                escalate over time. With 2024-2026 performance targets now in effect, buildings
                that miss the mark face significant penalties. We provide data-driven benchmarking
                that tracks your trajectory against these targets and identifies where you stand.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Vancouver -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
            <div class="shrink-0">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-navy-800 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="text-amber-400 font-heading font-bold text-lg">VAN</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-2">Vancouver, BC</h3>
              <p class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Deadline: June 1, 2026 | <a href="https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/environment/climate-change/clean-buildings/benchmark-bc" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:underline">Building Benchmark BC</a></p>
              <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed">
                Vancouver's reporting requirements sit within a broader provincial framework that is
                evolving alongside Canada's National Energy Code for Buildings (NECB). We bring
                cross-border expertise, understanding both the municipal disclosure requirements and
                the larger national policy direction that will shape future obligations.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Toronto -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
            <div class="shrink-0">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-navy-800 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="text-amber-400 font-heading font-bold text-lg">TOR</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-2">Toronto, ON</h3>
              <p class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Deadline: July 1, 2026 | <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/report-energy-and-water-use" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:underline">EWRB</a> / EGPS</p>
              <p class="text-navy-600 leading-relaxed">
                Ontario's Energy and Water Reporting and Benchmarking (EWRB) regulation and Toronto's
                Existing Building Energy Performance Standards (EGPS) create a layered compliance
                landscape. As our home market, we have deep expertise in navigating both the provincial
                and municipal requirements, and we understand the local utility data ecosystem.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TECHNICAL EDGE / TRUST SIGNALS -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-14">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-3">What Makes Us Different</h2>
        <p class="text-navy-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">We are not the cheapest option out there, but here is why our clients stick with us.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="p-8 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-amber-50 text-amber-600 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 font-bold">M&V</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy-800 text-lg mb-3">We Actually Check the Numbers</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            A lot of firms just enter data and hit submit. We are M&V specialists who apply IPMVP
            standards to every project. That means your numbers are solid and tell the real story
            of how your building is performing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-amber-50 text-amber-600 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy-800 text-lg mb-3">We Look at the Whole Picture</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Compliance is not just about carbon numbers. We keep an eye on health, safety, and
            regulatory requirements too, so nothing falls through the cracks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-amber-50 text-amber-600 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy-800 text-lg mb-3">12 Years and Counting</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            We have been doing this since 2014, working with teams like Macy's, Westfield, and
            Mandarin Oriental. Big building or small, you get the same level of care and attention.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CORE TO CANOPY -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-10">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy-800 mb-3">It Starts With Benchmarking</h2>
        <p class="text-navy-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Compliance gets your foot in the door, but the real value is what comes next. Here is the full range of what we can do together.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-slate-200">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-navy-800 text-white">
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-semibold text-sm">Core Compliance (Today's Campaign)</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-semibold text-sm">Full Lifecycle (Our Strength)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-700 text-sm">Regulated Benchmarking</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-500 text-sm">Energy Systems Planning</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-slate-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-700 text-sm">Utility Bill Analysis</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-500 text-sm">Program Design & Evaluation (EM&V)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-700 text-sm">M&V / Metering</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-500 text-sm">Design & Project Management</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-slate-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-700 text-sm">Energy Auditing</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-500 text-sm">Commissioning & Testing</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-700 text-sm">Regulatory Compliance</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-navy-500 text-sm">Procurement Design & Energy Economics</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-navy-400 text-sm mt-6">
        Curious how your benchmarking data can drive your next energy project? Just ask -- we love talking about this stuff.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-navy-800 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Not sure if your last filing was right?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-navy-200 text-lg mb-8">
        No worries -- grab a 15-minute call with us. We will take a look at your last submission and give you an honest assessment.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-700 transition-colors text-lg">
        Let's Have a Look
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
